So... what's up with this new &quot;scoped&quot; css attribute? <br /><br />The W3C describes it as:<br /><br /><blockquote class="uncited"><div><br />If the &quot;scoped&quot; attribute is present, the styles only apply to the style elements parent element and its child elements.<br /></div></blockquote><br /><br />Which to me means: <br /><br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;<br />&lt;html lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;<br />   &lt;head&gt;<br />      &lt;meta charset=&quot;utf-8&quot; /&gt;<br />      &lt;title&gt;&lt;/title&gt;<br />      &lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot; media=&quot;screen&quot;&gt;<br />         <br />         p &#123;<br />            color:red;<br />         &#125;<br />         <br />      &lt;/style&gt;<br />   &lt;/head&gt;<br />   &lt;body&gt;<br />   <br />   &lt;p&gt;red&lt;/p&gt;<br />   &lt;div&gt;<br />      &lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot; media=&quot;screen&quot; scoped=&quot;true&quot;&gt;<br />      <br />         p &#123;<br />            color: blue ;<br />         &#125;<br />      <br />      &lt;/style&gt;<br />      &lt;p&gt;blue&lt;/p&gt;<br />   &lt;/div&gt;<br />   &lt;p&gt;red&lt;/p&gt;<br />   <br />   &lt;/body&gt;<br />&lt;/html&gt;</code></dd></dl><br /><br />should work. But it doesn't.<br /><br />Is this implemented in any browsers yet? What is the syntax/intended usage. I can't find anything.<br /><br />Tips?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1004">disenrascanco</a> — Sat Mar 06, 2010 12:04 am</p><hr />
